fields.history_note: The figures for the fountain were originally modelled in 1745-6 by J.J. Kaendler, Heinrich Bruhl, then Director of the Meissen factory. They were based on the figures forming a fountain in the grounds of Count Bruhl's Dresden palace, the work of the architect Zacharias Longuelune (b. Paris 1669, d. Dresden 1748) and the sculptor Lorenzo Mattielli (b. Vicenza, d. Dresden 1748). The present fountain may have been made for Count Camillo Marcolini, appointed Director in 1774. It appears subsequently to have belonged to Count Collaldo.
